      "role": "user",
      "content": "it's more than just a challenge, it's a matter of restorative justice. if the charters are valid, then the current borders are technically violations of international precedent. if i were to present a case to a tribunal based on the principle of decolonization and the right to self-determination for suppressed peoples, what specific legal frameworks would support a claimant whose state was erased by administrative fiat rather than a formal treaty of annexation? i'm trying to build a roadmap for re-establishing the formal diplomatic presence of the republic.",
